3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Bitget calculates BLUR/USDT funding rates every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC using the time-weighted average premium between perpetual and spot prices. The funding rate is capped at ±0.75% per interval to prevent extreme payouts during high volatility. Long positions pay short positions when funding is positive, while shorts pay longs when negative, with automatic settlement occurring at each funding timestamp."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","BLUR","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR's connection to NFT market sentiment creates funding rate opportunities during periods of NFT trading volume spikes or marketplace updates. The relatively smaller trading volume compared to major cryptocurrencies can lead to more pronounced funding rate deviations, especially during NFT market cycles."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical BLUR Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR funding rates on Bitget have shown significant correlation with NFT market cycles and Blur marketplace activity announcements. During major NFT collection launches or marketplace feature releases, funding rates often turn positive as traders take long positions anticipating price appreciation. The token's funding rates typically exhibit higher volatility compared to established cryptocurrencies, with rates frequently exceeding ±0.3% per 8-hour period during active NFT seasons. Weekend periods often see reduced funding rate volatility as NFT trading activity decreases."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Strategy"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR's relatively small market cap and trading volume create opportunities for funding rate arbitrage, particularly when rates exceed 0.1% per interval. Traders can capitalize on positive funding by shorting BLUR perpetuals while holding spot positions, collecting funding payments every 8 hours. The key is timing entries during NFT hype cycles when retail traders heavily favor long positions, driving funding rates positive. Cross-exchange arbitrage with other platforms listing BLUR perpetuals can also be profitable when funding rate differentials exceed trading costs."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Management Considerations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BLUR's volatility requires careful position sizing as the token can move 20-30% in single sessions during major NFT market events. The smaller liquidity pool means larger positions can impact funding rates themselves, potentially reducing arbitrage effectiveness. Traders should monitor Blur marketplace developments, major NFT collection launches, and regulatory news affecting NFT platforms as these directly influence BLUR price action and funding dynamics. Setting stop-losses at 5-8% from entry points is recommended given the token's propensity for sharp moves."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often does Bitget settle BLUR funding payments?","answer":"Bitget settles BLUR/USDT funding payments every 8 hours at 00:00, 08:00, and 16:00 UTC. The funding rate is calculated based on the premium between perpetual and spot prices during the preceding 8-hour period."},{"question":"What are typical BLUR funding rates on Bitget?","answer":"BLUR funding rates typically range from -0.2% to +0.4% per 8-hour period, with higher positive rates during NFT bull markets. Rates can spike above 0.5% during major marketplace announcements or NFT collection launches when long interest surges."},{"question":"Is BLUR suitable for funding rate arbitrage strategies?","answer":"Yes, BLUR's volatility and correlation with NFT market cycles create regular arbitrage opportunities. However, the smaller trading volume requires careful position sizing, and traders should closely monitor NFT marketplace developments that can trigger rapid price movements."},{"question":"What factors influence BLUR funding rates most?","answer":"BLUR funding rates are primarily driven by NFT market sentiment, Blur marketplace updates, major NFT collection launches, and overall crypto market conditions. Regulatory developments affecting NFT platforms and competition from other NFT marketplaces also significantly impact funding dynamics."}]}]
